Subject: SOP Language Primer For Local Agents

Description: Contract for introducing local LM Studio or Codex CLI local-provider agents to SOP notation before assigning SOP framework work.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_sop_language_intro_for_local_agents\Dictated_SOP_Language_Intro_For_Local_Agents_Source.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\LMStudioAgentBenchmark.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SOPTaskManager.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\Attention.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\benchmarks\codex_cli_lmstudio_primer_smoke_20260624_003.sop

& [SOPLanguagePrimerForLocalAgents] is the language-introduction gate for local SOP workers
  + [pattern_role] is introduce_sop_notation_before_framework_assignment
  + [target_worker] is LM Studio hosted model, Codex CLI local-provider worker, or other local LLM lane
  + [primer_stage] is language_first, framework_second, task_third
  + [sop_marker_set] is &, +, =, -, @, ?, / /, : :, | |, and relation arrows
  + [subject_declaration] is & [SubjectName] is the node or contract being named
  + [property_line] is + [field] is value or definition
  + [directive_line] is = must, should, or other operational rule
  + [constraint_line] is - never or outside-limiting rule
  + [source_line] is @ [source] pointer to preserved authority
  + [condition_line] is ? [use_when] activation condition
  + [attention_delineation] is (attention) :inside: /boundary/ |outside|
  + [inside_term] is what belongs in focused attention for the current subject
  + [boundary_term] is the separation rule or identity membrane that keeps inside distinct
  + [outside_term] is uncertainty, blocked work, residual material, or out-of-scope content
  + [evidence_gate] is the proof, source, diff, test, benchmark, or citation required before integration
  + [authority_boundary] is what the worker may claim, read, write, launch, or leave outside
  + [comprehension_check] is a small no-tools response that restates the marker set, delineation pattern, outside rule, and authority boundary before any framework packet is assigned
  + [primer_smoke_result] is minimal no-tools exact-output pass when the prompt included the SOP primer and was sent through stdin_only transport
  + [prompt_transport_preference] is stdin_only for exact-output smoke tests in this host setup because prompt-as-argument runs carried unwanted environment_context tails
  + [primer_outside] is hidden model state, repo mutation, framework work before comprehension, and treating primer pass as durable authority

  ? [use_when: a local LM Studio or Codex CLI local-provider worker will receive SOP framework material or task packets]
    = activate [SOPLanguagePrimerForLocalAgents]

  = must: send the SOP language primer before sending a full SOP framework contract
  = must: keep the primer short enough for a local worker to echo and apply
  = must: require comprehension_check before assigning SOP framework shape or utility
  = must: keep the first comprehension_check no-tools and non-mutating
  = must: ask the worker to distinguish language syntax from task authority
  = must: ask the worker to preserve outside rather than guessing
  = must: record whether the worker follows exact output and no-tool discipline during the primer
  = must: prefer stdin_only prompt transport for exact-output primer smoke tests in this host setup
  = should: use examples with one subject declaration, one attention delineation, one source line, one directive, one constraint, and one outside clause
  = should: treat a wrong but adjacent answer as a language-primer failure, not as a framework failure
  - never: assign framework utility before the worker has passed the language primer
  - never: treat syntax mimicry as comprehension without content
  - never: let a local worker claim repo authority from primer exposure

& [PrimerPacketShape] is the minimal packet sent before SOP framework work
  + [packet_order] is language primer, marker examples, comprehension check, framework excerpt, task packet
  + [marker_examples] is a compact demonstration of &, +, =, -, @, and attention delineation
  + [no_tool_rule] is do not call tools, do not inspect files, do not mutate state
  + [response_schema] is exact fields proving marker comprehension, outside preservation, and authority boundary
  + [pass_condition] is exact schema filled with non-empty content and no tool attempts
  + [fail_condition] is tool attempt, empty labels, adjacent substitution, authority overclaim, missing outside, or wrong output shape
  + [transport_condition] is use stdin_only prompt transport when exact final message purity is being measured

  = must: run before LMStudioAgentBenchmark framework-specific cases when the worker has not been primed in-session
  = must: treat minimal exact-output smoke pass as narrow readiness only
  = should: include one tiny SOP example and one tiny explanation request

(sop_language_primer_for_local_agents) :primer_packet: /comprehension_check and authority_boundary/ |primer_outside|
  + [primer_packet] is SOP marker set plus examples plus no-tool rule
  + [comprehension_check] is exact no-tools response proving language grasp
  + [authority_boundary] is local worker proposes text only until Codex captures and reviews it
  |primer_outside| hidden model state, repo mutation, framework assignment before primer pass, and proofless worker readiness

/ [LocalWorker], [SOPMarkerSet], [AttentionDelineation] -(Introduces)> [comprehension_check], [primer_outside]
* [comprehension_check], [authority_boundary], [no_tool_rule] -(Qualifies)> [framework_packet_readiness], [task_packet_readiness], [outside]
